= The Austrian Issue

In coordination with the March on Berlin, which we have now resolved, Austrian forces had crossed the border into Bavaria to wage war. While their domestic allies no longer raise up arms against us, the Austrian issue remains ever prevalent. Under Hitler's call for a grand national revolution to unify the German people, the forces attempt to converge on Munich, assisted by domestic Nazi militias.

(WIP! SOON DONE!)